description:
&lt;h1&gt;Junior Sister/Charge Nurse - Chemotherapy Dau Unit - Band 6&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A fantastic career opportunity awaits you here at the Royal United Hospitals Chemotherapy Day Unit. Within this fast-paced environment care is delivered to both Haematology and Oncology patients as part of a wider inter-disciplinary team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic, experienced nurse with a background in cancer care ideally with knowledge and skills in Systemic Anti-Cancer Therapy (SACT). &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration with the senior nursing team to meet local and national targets is a fundamental aspect of this post to enable both individual and service progression in this dynamic speciality.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a band 6, you will be a clinical expert ensuring treatment is delivered in a highly professional, safe and holistic manner, whilst also supporting staff in their training and development. You will need to be highly motivated and able to demonstrate excellent clinical and interpersonal skills.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;There will be the opportunity to further both your clinical and managerial skills and knowledge and this will be tailored to your specific educational requirements, be that formal or informal.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our compassionate and dedicated team provide a friendly atmosphere, creating a welcoming environment where the patients’ experience is our focus.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you ready to embrace this diverse challenge, in a role which is both rewarding and fulfilling?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal visits are encouraged. Please contact Helen Bond or Hayley Beer, Senior Sisters:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monday - Friday 08.00 - 18.00 on 01225 824852&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
